My mom asked me a poignant question. 
-When you felt yourself dying, what did you fear?

I knew she wanted a religious answer, but it wasn't hell I feared.

I feared losing out on the life I hope to live, the friendship I've found, and the love. Cherish your life, no matter what

Out of respect to my friends who love me a lot, I will not keep everyone in the dark. This afternoon I almost died after a serious medical complication. It was very distressing for myself and for my father who had to watch it happen. I will be taking time off to rest. Much love.
